No matter what you don't miss, the concept of 50 unique routes, the sequence of races or anything else.
The idea of changing cars during a race is unusual.
You need to track the fuel along the way, because it's the ones your car can change, even though in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
The machines are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars are for straight sections of the road; and exotic super-sporters for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain routes.
The main mode of the story mode is closely linked to the challenge mode mode; it is a race on the individual plots that you will recognize on the course of the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points common to the challenges and story regimes.
Many opportunities are available for higher driving levels, starting with cars and ending with profiles.
In addition, the profile is related to Autolog online, which, among other things, compares the results you have achieved with the results of other players and provides communication with the public.
Here's another flaw that's difficult to understand; this is an example from the last race in sequence.
You and your car get into a tunnel subway (let's take it this way) where you run down the tracks in the dark (let's say so).
Your speedometer shows the numbers from 150 to 200 km/h (let's take it this way) when suddenly a subway train strikes you to turn your car into a chest of scrap metal.
For a few days, our editorial discussed whether, at the time of the creation of the game, no one thought for a second, or its creators really thought of us as such.
The technical composition of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video is mostly pleasant, sometimes even amazing.
Although it is regrettable that, at some critical points, the quality of the writing is sometimes quite severe, the quality of the writing is declining.
This is particularly true of accidents involving a large number of participants, where a good record would not be particularly helpful to you either.
Sound's fine; sound's a lover's sound.
In order to please the widest possible youth audience, the soundtrack 'composed compositions from different styles'; but hardly many people buy the game because of its music.
Overall impression of Need for Speed: Running pretty messy.
If the game were to avoid manifestly unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say that Run is the best part of NFS in the last few years.
In any case, the game leaves the feeling of inadequacy.
